  "title": "Cargo Coordinator (Joining bonus of $5000)",
  "description": "<p>Cargo Coordinator<br />Location: Changi<br />Joining Bonus: Up to <strong>$5,000</strong></p><p>Join a dynamic logistics environment at Changi and play a key role in ensuring smooth and timely cargo operations for airlines and logistics partners.</p><h3><strong>Job Highlights</strong></h3><ul><li>Permanent shift (Morning / Afternoon / Night)</li><li>6-day work week</li><li>Up to <strong>$5,000 joining bonus</strong> (terms apply)</li></ul><h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Handle cargo shipments in the warehouse, either manually or using a forklift, together with a team of Cargo Handlers.</li><li>Check documentation and real-time system data to ensure compliance with procedures and regulations.</li><li>Attend to airlines’ and third-party agents’ enquiries, including follow-ups on operational issues.</li><li>Supervise and be responsible for a team of Cargo Handlers, ensuring cargo is loaded and unloaded on time.</li><li>Ensure all cargo operations comply with safety, security, and operational requirements.</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Minimum <strong>Diploma</strong> OR at least <strong>1 year of warehouse / cargo operations experience</strong>.</li><li>Supervisory or team-leading skills.</li><li>Able to multitask and communicate effectively with airlines and third parties.</li><li>Able to work <strong>permanent shift</strong> and <strong>6 days per week</strong>.</li><li>Able to lift heavy objects.</li><li>Willing to learn and operate a forklift (training provided)</li></ul><h3><strong>How to Apply</strong></h3><p>Apply Now for a quicker response.<br />We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p><p><strong>K. Keshika Samantha (R26159509)</strong><br /><strong>Just Recruit Singapore Pte Ltd (EA12C6295)</strong></p>",
